710753f-a.title: Manhattan: 12th Avenue - 34th Street
710753f-a.text:
12th Avenue, at the N. E. corner of W. 34th Street and north-
eastward. Shown at the corner is a diner under the New York Central
Railroad's elevated roadbed. View 2 is the area that adjoins this
to the north, showing the yards there.
Incidently this site was formerly the rear entrance to that
V shaped row of structures that constituted the old Manhattan Market
of 1871. This was completely removed tn 1936.
August 24, 1940
Views 1,2
P. L. Sperr
N4O REPRODITRIO

710754f-a.title: Manhattan: 12th Avenue - 34th Street
710754f-a.text:
12th Avenue, west side, north from W. 34th Street (Pier ~74),
showing the shack housing the Dockmasters office, the coal banks on
the pier to the north and the West Side Highway.
View 2 is limited to the coal btnks of Henry Hencken.
August 24, 1940
Views 1,2
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS
